H(S|\hat{S}) \leq K \cdot h(P_e)
 P_E = Pr( S \ne \hat{S})
H(S|\hat{S}) \leq h(P_E) + P_E \log_2(|\mathcal{X}| - 1)
P_E \le \sum P(S_i \ne \hat{S_i})= K P_e
|\mathcal{X}|\le 2^K
K P_e < 1/2
h(\dot)
H(S|\hat{S}) \leq h(K P_e) + K P_e  \log_2(|\mathcal{X}| - 1) \leq h(K P_e) + K^2 P_e 
h(K P_e) \le K h(P_e)
H(S|\hat{S}) \leq K h(P_e) + K^2 P_e 
P_e \ll 2^{-K}\ll 1
